<HEAD>Key Provisions of Accord</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Also in Saturday AMs report.</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-East-West, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Key provisions of the human rights accord tentatively approved Friday by 35 nations at the <LOCATION> Helsinki </LOCATION> review conference:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 _ To give prisoners humane treatment, and stop the abuse of psychiatry against political prisoners; _ To decide outstanding emigration applications within six months, applications for <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> bloc citizens to join Western spouses within three months, for family reunions within one month, and for urgent medical travel or funeral attendance within three days; _ To allow religious education, the dissemination of religious literature and church charity; _ To encourage tourism, particularly by allowing Western tourists to stay in <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> bloc homes; _ To allow freer spread of information, halting <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> bloc jamming of Western radio stations; _ To stop expelling journalists or taking other measures against them over the content of their reports; _ To allow independent groups to monitor their governments' human rights behavior and action on the environment; _ To exchange much more economic data to facilitate Western business with the <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>; _ To publish widely the text of the <LOCATION> Helsinki </LOCATION> Final Act, the <LOCATION> Vienna </LOCATION> document and conditions for emigration or travel abroad; and _ To hold annual conferences on human rights, and to allow any <LOCATION> Helsinki </LOCATION> signatory to raise human rights affairs on a bilateral level with any other signatory state.
</TEXT>
