<HEAD>Six-Year-Old Bills Fan Gets Back Stolen Flag And More</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TONAWANDA, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Kind-hearted thieves returned first-grader <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON> <PERSON> Allen </PERSON>'s prized Buffalo Bills flag and gave her some goodies to boot. The 6-year-old girl had proudly displayed the deep blue Bills flag inscribed with the words `` Happy New Year'' under the American flag outside her family's home just north of <LOCATION> Buffalo </LOCATION> until last weekend, when it disappeared. Whoever took it left a note in the family's mailbox promising to return the flag after the Bills-Bengals American Football Conference Championship game in <LOCATION> Cincinnati </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON> watched Sunday's game, which the Bills lost, on television and thought she spotted the flag in the crowd. She waited and waited, but the flag did n't show up. After news reports about her loss, the family received a mysterious phone call Wednesday evening. The caller instructed the family to look for the flag near a telephone junction box outside their home, said <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON>'s father, <PERSON> Peter </PERSON>. The family found the flag, a case of beer, a thank-you note, a bag and a second note that read, `` We waited till now to return the flag for our own protection -LRB- we thought you'd be watching -RRB-, but we had all intentions of returning your flag. And this is for <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON>.'' Inside the bag, to <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON>'s surprise and delight, was a game program from <LOCATION> Cincinnati </LOCATION>, a shirt, a hat and several other souvenirs from the playoff. `` I still do n't know who took it,'' <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> said, `` but they certainly have made my little girl happy. She really is kind of speechless after all that's happened.''
