ION> Miami </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>. Jan. 22, but now will require six weeks of repair A <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Parcel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> cargo bin blew into a <ORGANIZATION> Southwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> 737, putting a six-inch gash in the fuselage near the cockpit, said <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Kochevar </PERSON>, assistant airport manager.
