7 with <ORGANIZATION> ANC </ORGANIZATION> leader <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> <PERSON> Tambo </PERSON>, and <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> officials maintain contacts with the group. The <ORGANIZATION> ANC </ORGANIZATION> also has support among liberals in <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>, but conservatives condemn the group as a communist organization armed by the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>. The Pentagon book says the <ORGANIZATION> ANC </ORGANIZATION> is armed with Soviet weapons and gets most of its training in Marxist-oriented <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION>. The South African government in 1960 banned the then-peaceful <ORGANIZATION> ANC </ORGANIZATION>, and one year later the group began a sabotage campaign. In recent years the <ORGANIZATION> ANC </ORGANIZATION>'s attacks have expanded to include random bombings in busy public places such as fast-food restaurants and bus depots. There have been 180 bombings in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> over the past 31 months, killing 35 people and injuring at least 665.
