 The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>, in a report on deductions that was part of a recent series of articles on the federal income tax, said scientology fees are not deductible. The <ORGANIZATION> Internal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revenue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> considers scientology fees non-deductible personal expenses, but appellate courts for the 2nd, 6th and 8th circuits have ruled the fees are deductible charitable contributions. Those cases are under appeal, and if the <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> sides with the <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Scientology </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> IRS </ORGANIZATION> will have to allow the deductions.
