<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Mayor <PERSON> Annette </PERSON> <PERSON> Strauss </PERSON> on Friday announced her candidacy for a second term as the leader of the nation's seventh-largest city, a day after a mayoral commission released its plan to stem racial tensions `` <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> is on the move again,'' said Mrs. <PERSON> Strauss </PERSON>, 64, the city's first elected woman mayor. `` We've regained the momentum of the'60s,'70s and early'80s.'' The mayor said she has worked hard to promote the city as a good place to do business. `` <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> is the best place anywhere for businesses to succeed,'' she said, but conceded that <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> has been losing tax base to its suburbs. `` At the top of my list of priorities are fighting crime and drugs and economic development, which I believe are inextricably tied together.'' The second year of her first two-year term as mayor was one of the most violent in the city's history. Five <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> police officers were killed and the city recorded a record number of homicides. She said progress has been made toward easing racial tensions and praised the work of <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> Together, a 76-member commission she appointed to study race relations in the wake of the police shootings and a dispute over the role of the <ORGANIZATION> Dallas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Police </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Citizens </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Review </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION>. The commission issued a report Thursday that recommended the appointment of a charter review committee to study the number and composition of city council districts. <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION>' <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> is now comprised of the mayor, two at-large members and eight district members. Expensive campaigns keep many people from running for city office, <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> Together said. Mrs. <PERSON> Strauss </PERSON> spent about $ 1.2 million on her mayoral race in 1987, but she said she would not spend that much for the May 6 election. She is the only announced candidate for the post. Mrs. <PERSON> Strauss </PERSON> served two terms as an at-large City Council member and defeated <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON> in a runoff for mayor in 1987. The incumbent, <PERSON> Starke </PERSON> <PERSON> Taylor </PERSON>, did not run. A public relations consultant, Mrs. <PERSON> Strauss </PERSON> has been active in <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> civic and performing arts organizations for more than 20 years.
