and produces about 240,000 cars annually. _ <ORGANIZATION> Toyota </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Manufacturing </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> U.S.A. </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Georgetown </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ky. </LOCATION>, was dedicated in October. It has about 1,750 employees and produces about 360 Camry sedans a day. By the end of 1989, it will produce 200,000 cars annually and have 3,000 employees. An additional 500 workers will be added when a power train plant that produces engines, axles and steering components becomes operational in 1991. _ <ORGANIZATION> Nissan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Manufacturing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. <LOCATION> U.S.A. </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Smyrna </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tenn. </LOCATION>, opened in June 1983 and has 3,100 workers The plant produces about 220,000 Sentra cars and <ORGANIZATION> Nissan </ORGANIZATION> light trucks annually. _ <ORGANIZATION> Honda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Manufacturing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Marysville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, began making motorcycles in 1979. Auto production started in 1982. The company now has two plants at <LOCATION> Marysville </LOCATION> and one at <PERSON> Anna </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>. It has expanded at <PERSON> Anna </PERSON> and is building a fourth plant in East Liberty, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>. The workforce is 6,700 and expected to increase to 8,500 by 1991. This year, <ORGANIZATION> Honda </ORGANIZATION> is expected to produce 360,000 Accord and Civic cars, as well as motorcycles.
