<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices strengthened at midday Friday, led higher by a burst of institutional buying. The market also was cheered on by the strong trend in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> earlier Friday and in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> on Thursday, traders said. Dealers said there were patches of active trading at midmorning, with some large institutions snapping up some shares they considered to be bargains. The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was up 6.4 points, or 0.3 percent, at 1,857.3 around 12:15 p.m. local time. Midday volume totaled 487.8 million shares, compared with 548.1 million Thursday.
