 <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Westminster </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION> said its <ORGANIZATION> U.S.-based </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Natwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Government </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> would abandon its primary bond dealership after operating in the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Treasuries market in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> for just over three months. <ORGANIZATION> Natwest </ORGANIZATION> said some of the 100 people employed by the dealership might be transferred within the company. The decision to withdraw resulted from an assessment of the costs involved in the primary dealership, <ORGANIZATION> Natwest </ORGANIZATION> said. `` Continued expansion of the business would require the injection of substantial additional capital, but analysis of the prospective long-term return on capital has persuaded us that further investment can not be justified in the context of our overall strategy,'' <ORGANIZATION> Natwest </ORGANIZATION> said in a statement. County <ORGANIZATION> Natwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Government </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> was named one of 46 primary dealers in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government securities on Sept. 29, the last time new primary dealers were added to the list by the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>. In December, the <ORGANIZATION> Fed </ORGANIZATION> recommended that <ORGANIZATION> Natwest </ORGANIZATION> inject $ 50 million to $ 100 million into the dealership to meet capitalization requirements. Primary dealers are government bond dealers that do business directly with the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>. They are required to make markets in all government issues and to participate at all Treasury auctions.
